ly discounted at $2,300 for a 2022 config with a Ryzen 9 6900HX, RTX 3080 Ti and 165Hz display.</p><h2> Acer Nitro 5 </h2><p><core-commerce id="05f0835c38d441e8941fe67042e35c21" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> The <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:103;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMEJTTFdHRlhEP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTFjOC0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMTI0ZTlmOTktYWVkOC00ZDQwLWJjMjAtMjRhYmE3ZjJlZjE3In0&amp;signature=AQAAARaRUG1g2TORtc0dTHdIErQiG017v2D3gWygF6LSdpm-&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0BSLWGFXD" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0BSLWGFXD?th=1" class="rapid-with-clickid">Acer Nitro 5</a> is the runner up pick in our guide to the <a data-i13n="cpos:104;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-budget-gaming-laptop-130004199.html">best budget gaming laptops</a> , and right now a configuration with a Core i5-12500H, GeForce RTX 3050 Ti, 144Hz 1080p display, 16GB of RAM and 512GB is available for $740. That&#39;s a new low and roughly $160 off this model&#39;s typical street price. This is a chunky plastic machine, and you&#39;ll need to ratchet down the settings in certain games <a data-i13n="cpos:105;pos:1" href="https://www.tomshardware.com/reviews/acer-nitro-5-2022-review-gaming-under-dollar1000">to hit</a> a <a data-i13n="cpos:106;pos:1" href="https://www.pcmag.com/reviews/acer-nitro-5-2022-12th-gen-core">decent frame rate</a> . But getting a 144Hz display and enough power to keep up with modern games is a plus at this price. As an affordable yet competent entry point to PC gaming, it&#39;s a fine value.</p><p><strong><em>您的 Prime 会员日购物指南</em></stron